# AmeriList design system

Follow `design-system/AMERILIST-DESIGN-SYSTEM.md` when styling this Next.js site.

## Typography
- **Plus Jakarta Sans** (400–800), not Raleway unless user asks otherwise
- Body: 15px / 1.65, color `#7d8087`
- Hero H1: weight 800, letter-spacing -1.5px; accent `#81e92f` (lime)

## Colors
- Primary `#074eb9`, bright `#0070ab`
- Navy hero `#252840`, footer `#1e2033`
- Surface/header `#eff2f9`
- CTA gradient: `linear-gradient(90deg, #0070ab 0%, #e31937 100%)`

## Components
- Gradient pill primary CTA, white secondary, sticky header on surface
- Max content width ~1120px
- Map tokens into Tailwind/CSS variables in `app/globals.css`

Do not invent a new palette unless the user explicitly asks to diverge.
